{
  "stem": "26111.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Henry Warner Laurant, formerly Hans Werner Levy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All of them?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] All right.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Henry is Henry with a Y; Warner, W-A-R-N-E-R; Laurant, L-A-U-R-A-N-T.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my original name had the same initials and was instead of Henry, Hans, H-A-N-S; instead of Warner, Werner, W-E-R-N-E-R; instead of Laurant, Levy, L-E-V-Y.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "May 28, 1924.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "72--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--almost 73.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In what was then called Konigsberg, the capital of East-- province of East Prussia in Germany.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "K-O-E-N-I-G-S-B-E-R-G.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Immediately following the Second World War, it was annexed to the-- it was part of the [SIGHS] eastern half of East Prussia, which was annexed to Russia.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That-- I'm saying Russia because it's not the USSR, not the Soviet Union it was an annexed to, but the Russian Republic.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that means that even though now the USSR has disappeared as a federation, it is-- the, the area in which Konigsberg-- then Konigsberg was located still belongs as an integral part of the Russian Republic.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now called Kaliningrad, by the way.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father was Walter Levy and my mother was Erna Levy, nee Behrendt.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "B-E-H-R-E-N-D-T.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not-- yes, when I was born, I had a sister two years older than myself, Anneliese, A-N-N-E-L-I-E-S-E.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she was born in July of 1922, [SIGHS] so just, just short of two years before me.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yes, indeed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I guess the earliest would be-- this was a very, very old town at that time.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I say at that time because it was totally destroyed during the war and then rebuilt by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But at that time, it was a very historic town with old buildings.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I recall very well that we had an apartment which looked out over what was called the Palace Lake.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a palace on a hill, all very Ruritanian type.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
